<rdg source="bib:Coedes1937-1966_01">munināsa liṅgaṁ</rdg>
                   
<note>Cœdès' assumption of a verb form 
<foreign>āsa</foreign> here seems unsatisfactory. In the context, 
<foreign>suliṅgam</foreign> would be suitable, as shown by parallels in contemporary inscriptions (
<ref target="K0077.xml">K. 77</ref>, st. III and 
<ref target="K0582.xml">K. 582</ref>, st. I), and we adopt this reading even though it is rather uncertain that a vowel marker 
<foreign>u</foreign> was actually ever engraved below the 
<foreign>s</foreign>.</note>
                                     </app>
                 
