<note>We tentatively assume that the hypermetrical 
<foreign>śrī-</foreign> was not intended to be part of the verse. Another way to resolve the metrical irregularity would be to correct 
<foreign>some</foreign> to 
<foreign>se</foreign>. The name 
<foreign>prabhāseśvara</foreign> is found in some contemporary Campā inscriptions (
<ref target="C0081.xml">C. 81</ref>, face C, l. 2; 
<ref target="C0087.xml">C. 87</ref>, st. II; and three times in 
<ref target="C0096.xml">C. 96</ref>).</note>
